# Creative Systems Specification

## Purpose

Define comprehensive creative and artistic systems as the Body component of the Cathedral's Trinity Architecture, providing professional-grade tools for painting, sculpture, digital art, and collaborative creation. Integrate with sacred mathematics, trauma-safe design, and the living grimoire narrative through Arcana-based character selection and Solfeggio frequency mapping.

## Requirements

### Requirement: Professional Studio Spaces

The system SHALL provide 5 distinct professional studio spaces optimized for different artistic mediums with proper equipment, lighting, ventilation, and safety protocols.

#### Scenario: Painting Atelier Access

- **WHEN** artists require painting workspace

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide Master Painting Atelier with 12-person capacity, easels, palette stations, professional paints, canvas storage, drying racks, color mixing stations, reference library, model stand, north-facing natural light, full-spectrum LED panels, track lighting, and safety protocols

#### Scenario: Sculpture Workshop Usage

- **WHEN** artists need sculpture workspace

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide Master Sculpture Workshop with 8-person capacity, modeling stands, clay stations, armature materials, sculpting tools, kiln access, welding station, stone carving area, power tools, casting equipment, and safety protocols

#### Scenario: Digital Arts Laboratory Access

- **WHEN** artists require digital workspace

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide Digital Arts Laboratory with 16-person capacity, high-end workstations, graphics tablets, 3D printers, VR headsets, large-format displays, color-calibrated monitors, digital cameras, scanners, motion capture, render farm, and precision climate control

### Requirement: Comprehensive Material Library

The system SHALL maintain a professional-grade material library with 500+ art supplies including pigments, supports, tools, and equipment with quality grades, safety information, and supplier details.

#### Scenario: Professional Painting Materials

- **WHEN** painters need specific materials

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide professional-grade materials including cadmium pigments, Belgian linen canvases, Kolinsky sable brushes, with archival quality, proper storage requirements, and safety protocols

#### Scenario: Sculpture Materials Access

- **WHEN** sculptors require materials

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide clay types, bronze alloys, carving tools, foundry equipment, with professional grade classifications, usage notes, and safety procedures

#### Scenario: Digital Art Tools

- **WHEN** digital artists need equipment

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide pressure-sensitive styluses, high-end tablets, professional monitors, with specifications, compatibility information, and ergonomic guidelines

### Requirement: Technique Database and Learning System

The system SHALL provide comprehensive technique database with tutorial steps, historical context, and skill progression for all artistic mediums.

#### Scenario: Painting Technique Learning

- **WHEN** artists want to learn specific techniques

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide detailed tutorials for alla prima, glazing, impasto, with materials needed, time requirements, key principles, historical masters, modern applications, and step-by-step instructions

#### Scenario: Sculpture Mastery Development

- **WHEN** artists progress in sculpture skills

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide advanced techniques including lost wax casting, direct carving, with expert-level difficulty, foundry safety, material understanding, and tool control principles

#### Scenario: Digital Art Skills Building

- **WHEN** artists develop digital capabilities

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide digital painting, 3D modeling tutorials, with intermediate to advanced difficulty, software requirements, and modern industry applications

### Requirement: Collaboration and Project Management

The system SHALL provide structured collaboration tools enabling artist networking, project coordination, skill sharing, and mentorship programs.

#### Scenario: Artist Collaboration Matching

- **WHEN** artists seek collaboration opportunities

- **THEN** the system SHALL analyze complementary skills, medium compatibility, skill level differences, and style synergy to recommend optimal collaboration partners and project types

#### Scenario: Project Coordination

- **WHEN** multiple artists work together

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide milestone tracking, resource allocation, deadline management, progress visualization, and team communication tools

#### Scenario: Critique and Learning

- **WHEN** artists need feedback and skill development

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide structured peer review sessions, mentorship matching, workshop scheduling, technique demonstrations, and portfolio development tools

### Requirement: Exhibition and Gallery Systems

The system SHALL provide multiple gallery spaces for showcasing artwork with professional presentation, climate control, security, and curatorial support.

#### Scenario: Main Gallery Exhibition

- **WHEN** artists need prominent display

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide main gallery (40x30x12 feet) with museum-quality LED track system, 150 linear feet of wall capacity, 20 pedestals for sculpture, temperature/humidity control, and 24/7 monitoring

#### Scenario: Digital Gallery Access

- **WHEN** digital artists need display

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide digital gallery with 4K ultra-wide displays, touch and gesture control, simultaneous multi-artist display, static images, video art, interactive installations, and online virtual viewing

#### Scenario: Curatorial Support

- **WHEN** planning exhibitions

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide theme development, artist selection, spatial planning, 3D layout visualization, catalog production, artwork handling, lighting design, and opening coordination

### Requirement: Commission Marketplace

The system SHALL provide structured commission and freelance marketplace connecting artists with clients across multiple mediums and price ranges.

#### Scenario: Portrait Commission System

- **WHEN** clients request portraits

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide commission types (sketch $200-500, painting $800-3000, digital $300-1200), timelines (1-8 weeks), requirements (reference photos, size specifications, style preferences), and artist matching

#### Scenario: Architectural Art Commission

- **WHEN** clients need large-scale art

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide architectural art commissions (small sculpture $1500-5000, large installation $10000-50000), planning and creation timelines (2-20 weeks), site survey requirements, and permit assistance

#### Scenario: Illustration Work

- **WHEN** clients need illustrations

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide editorial illustration ($300-1500), book cover design ($800-3000), concept art ($500-2000), with concept development, creation timelines, and usage rights management

### Requirement: Merkaba 3D Sacred Geometry Builder

The system SHALL provide real-time 3D Merkaba (Star Tetrahedron) builder with sacred geometry accuracy, divine/infernal rotation, and Godot export capabilities.

#### Scenario: Sacred Geometry Creation

- **WHEN** creating mystical artwork

- **THEN** the system SHALL generate perfect Merkaba structures using golden ratio proportions, interlocking tetrahedrons with configurable size, rotation speeds, and color schemes (divine gold, infernal crimson)

#### Scenario: Real-time 3D Manipulation

- **WHEN** artists work with Merkaba structures

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide real-time rotation with divine clockwise and infernal counterclockwise motion, adjustable parameters, and live vertex position updates

#### Scenario: Godot Integration Export

- **WHEN** integrating with game development

- **THEN** the system SHALL export Merkaba as Godot MeshInstance code with proper 3D coordinates, materials, and rotation scripts for seamless game integration

### Requirement: Professional Brush Engine with Dynamics

The system SHALL provide DaVinci-quality brush engine with pressure sensitivity, fusion kink color response, and professional painting capabilities.

#### Scenario: Professional Brush Dynamics

- **WHEN** executing brush strokes

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide brush dynamics including pressure opacity, pressure size, velocity size, tilt angle, rotation, jitter, and scatter with configurable parameters

#### Scenario: Fusion Kink Color Response

- **WHEN** applying fusion influence to brush work

- **THEN** the system SHALL modify colors based on divine/infernal affinity with lightening/gold for divine influence, darkening/red for infernal influence, and balanced harmony response

#### Scenario: Frequency Modulation

- **WHEN** creating audio-reactive artwork

- **THEN** the system SHALL modulate brush properties based on Solfeggio frequencies (396-963 Hz) with real-time audio analysis and visual response

### Requirement: 22 Major Arcana Character Integration

The system SHALL provide complete 22 Major Arcana character system for game start customization with unique frequency signatures and personality traits.

#### Scenario: Arcana Character Selection

- **WHEN** initializing creative sessions

- **THEN** the system SHALL present 22 Major Arcana (Themela Fool through World) with unique frequencies (396-963 Hz), divine/infernal affinity profiles, and visual customization options

#### Scenario: Daimon Configuration

- **WHEN** setting up Arcana character

- **THEN** the system SHALL configure character with frequency signature, divine affinity (0.0-1.0), infernal affinity (0.0-1.0), harmony balance calculation, primary/secondary/aura colors, and geometry pattern preferences

#### Scenario: Frequency Mapping to Visuals

- **WHEN** converting Arcana frequencies to visual elements

- **THEN** the system SHALL map Solfeggio frequencies to RGB colors, sacred geometry patterns (Flower of Life, Fibonacci spiral, Merkaba), and aura effects for consistent mystical visualization

### Requirement: Vector Graphics with Infinite Resolution

The system SHALL provide professional vector graphics engine with infinite resolution, sacred geometry tools, and golden ratio alignment.

#### Scenario: Sacred Geometry Vector Creation

- **WHEN** creating mathematical artwork

- **THEN** the system SHALL generate perfect circles, Flower of Life patterns, Fibonacci spirals using Bezier curves with golden ratio alignment and sacred mathematics precision

#### Scenario: Infinite Resolution Scaling

- **WHEN** scaling vector artwork

- **THEN** the system SHALL maintain perfect quality at any size using vector math rather than raster limitations, suitable for both digital display and large-format printing

#### Scenario: Professional Vector Tools

- **WHEN** creating complex vector compositions

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide professional vector tools including perfect circle creation, Bezier curve manipulation, path editing, and geometry-specific tools for sacred form creation

### Requirement: Trauma-Safe Creative Interface

The system SHALL implement comprehensive trauma safety and neurodivergent accessibility throughout all creative interfaces and tools.

#### Scenario: Emergency Exit Options

- **WHEN** users feel overwhelmed or need to exit

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide immediate ESC key functionality, obvious exit buttons, and escape routes from all interface states without unexpected behaviors

#### Scenario: Motion and Sensory Controls

- **WHEN** users need sensory accommodation

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide motion reduction options, adjustable animation speeds, high contrast modes, and complete ability to disable all motion effects

#### Scenario: Processing Time Accommodation

- **WHEN** users need time to process

- **THEN** the system SHALL provide generous timeouts, pause options, no forced progress, and clear indicators of time remaining for any time-sensitive operations

